MainMenu, ToolBar and TabMenu editingYou can edit the menus in FlashDevelop thru their corresponding xml files from the FlashDevelop setting folder.The actual editing is easy but there are certain things you have to know before you start customizing your menus:There are some dynamic variables that you can use with this file. Read moreSample menu:<menu label="SampleMenu" name="NameOfTheSampleMenu"><button label="Google" click="RunProcess" tag="http://www.google.com/" /><button label="MTASC" click="RunProcessCaptured" tag="C:\MTASC\mtasc.exe;argument_string_here" /></menu>Item nodenames:Menu = "menu"Button = "button"CheckBox = "checkbox"ComboBox = "combobox"* Main xml element can use any name desired.List of item attributes:label - Label of the itemname - Name of the itemclick - Click event handler's name *propertychanged - Property changed event handler's nametag - Arguments should be inserted hereshortcut - Valid Microsoft.NET shortcutimage - Index of the image to display (in settings/Images.png)enabled - Is the item enabled (true/false)visible - Is the item visible (true/false)* Not available for menu item.List of usable methods:RunProcess - Runs a simple process. Arguments: file path or url.RunProcessCaptured - Runs a complex process. Arguments: "file;arguments".PluginCommand - Calls a plugin command. Arguments: custom string.* There also lots of other methods that are not that useful like basic Cut or Paste commands.